You can use OVF TOOL that is a command line program that comes with VMWare

just move to the path

cd /Applications/VMware\ Fusion.app/Contents/Library/VMware\ OVF\ Tool/

then run this command:

./ovftool --acceptAllEulas ~/Documents/Virtual\ Machines.localized/Windows\ 7.vmwarevm/Windows\ 7.vmx ~/Documents/Win7.ova

changing according to your vm and the destionation folder with the final .ova


done!

Now you can import even in VMWare ESXi
